## `<file-level: options structs>`
<!-- checksum: rust-mkfs-1 -->

### Purpose
Python's keyword arguments become Rust `Options` structs with `Default` impls. Two: `MkfsOptions` for first-time creation, `OpenOptions` for subsequent opens.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};
use std::time::Duration;

use rusqlite::{Connection, OpenFlags, params};

use crate::errors::{Error, Result};
use crate::fs::Filesystem;
use crate::schema::{
    apply_pragmas, install_schema, DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE, ROOT_INODE, SyncMode,
};

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct MkfsOptions {
    pub chunk_size: i64,
    pub overwrite:  bool,
    pub owner_uid:  Option<u32>,
    pub owner_gid:  Option<u32>,
}

impl Default for MkfsOptions {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            chunk_size: DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE,
            overwrite:  false,
            owner_uid:  None,
            owner_gid:  None,
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default)]
pub struct OpenOptions {
    pub readonly:            bool,
    pub uid:                 Option<u32>,
    pub gid:                 Option<u32>,
    pub sync_mode:           SyncMode,            // plan.v7: Default = Normal
    pub checkpoint_interval: Option<Duration>,    // tier-5: not used yet
}
```

---

## `pub fn mkfs(path: &Path, opts: MkfsOptions) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-mkfs-2 -->

### Purpose
Create a new sqlite-fs database file at `path`. Installs schema, inserts root directory owned by the caller's euid/egid (unless explicit owner ids are given).

### Preconditions
- `opts.chunk_size` positive (typically a power of two).

### Postconditions
- File exists at `path`.
- All tables per `schema::DDL` present.
- `schema_version` has one row `(SCHEMA_VERSION=2, chunk_size)`.
- `nodes` has one row for root: `inode=ROOT_INODE=1`, `kind='dir'`, `mode=0o755`, `uid=owner_uid or euid`, `gid=owner_gid or egid`, `nlink=2`.

### Failure Modes
- `path` exists && `!opts.overwrite`: `Err(Error::AlreadyExists)`.
- I/O errors removing existing file → `Err(Error::Sqlite)` by bubble (not quite right; a follow-up engspec will promote these to `Error::Io`).
- rusqlite errors propagate.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn mkfs(path: &Path, opts: MkfsOptions) -> Result<()> {
    if path.exists() {
        if !opts.overwrite {
            return Err(Error::AlreadyExists(
                format!("file exists: {}", path.display())
            ));
        }
        let _ = std::fs::remove_file(path);
        // Sidecar WAL/SHM files can linger — wipe them too.
        for suffix in ["-wal", "-shm"] {
            let base = path.file_name().map(|s| s.to_string_lossy().into_owned())
                .unwrap_or_default();
            let side = path.with_file_name(format!("{base}{suffix}"));
            let _ = std::fs::remove_file(side);
        }
    }

    let conn = Connection::open(path)?;
    apply_pragmas(&conn, SyncMode::Full)?;   // full sync for the one-time mkfs commit
    install_schema(&conn, opts.chunk_size)?;

    let owner_uid = opts.owner_uid.unwrap_or_else(|| unsafe { libc::geteuid() });
    let owner_gid = opts.owner_gid.unwrap_or_else(|| unsafe { libc::getegid() });

    let now = std::time::SystemTime::now()
        .duration_since(std::time::UNIX_EPOCH)
        .map(|d| d.as_nanos() as i64).unwrap_or(0);

    conn.execute(
        "INSERT INTO nodes (inode, kind, mode, uid, gid, size,
                            atime_ns, mtime_ns, ctime_ns, nlink)
         VALUES (?1, 'dir', ?2, ?3, ?4, 0, ?5, ?5, ?5, 2)",
        params![ROOT_INODE as i64, 0o755i64, owner_uid, owner_gid, now],
    )?;
    Ok(())
}
```

