## `pub fn open_fs(path: &Path, opts: OpenOptions) -> Result<Filesystem>`
<!-- checksum: rust-mkfs-3 -->

### Purpose
Open an existing sqlite-fs database. In tier 4, `checkpoint_interval` is stored on `OpenOptions` but not acted on; tier 5 adds the background thread.

### Postconditions
- Returns a `Filesystem` with PRAGMAs applied per `opts.sync_mode`.
- `readonly=true` opens the connection with `SQLITE_OPEN_READ_ONLY`.
- Effective uid/gid default to current euid/egid.

### Failure Modes
- File not a valid SQLite DB → `Error::Sqlite`. **propagated**.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn open_fs(path: &Path, opts: OpenOptions) -> Result<Filesystem> {
    let conn = if opts.readonly {
        Connection::open_with_flags(
            path,
            OpenFlags::SQLITE_OPEN_READ_ONLY | OpenFlags::SQLITE_OPEN_URI,
        )?
    } else {
        Connection::open(path)?
    };

    // Apply pragmas: on readonly, journal_mode=WAL is already persisted at mkfs time
    // (it's a persistent pragma) and re-issuing may fail on a RO conn; guard by checking.
    apply_pragmas_maybe_readonly(&conn, opts.sync_mode, opts.readonly)?;

    let uid = opts.uid.unwrap_or_else(|| unsafe { libc::geteuid() });
    let gid = opts.gid.unwrap_or_else(|| unsafe { libc::getegid() });

    let mut fs = Filesystem::new(conn, opts.readonly, uid, gid)?;
    if let Some(interval) = opts.checkpoint_interval {
        fs.start_checkpoint(path.to_path_buf(), interval);
    }
    Ok(fs)
}

fn apply_pragmas_maybe_readonly(
    conn: &Connection, sync_mode: SyncMode, readonly: bool,
) -> Result<()> {
    // journal_mode / synchronous are persistent on the WAL file and write-only;
    // skip them on readonly opens.
    if !readonly {
        apply_pragmas(conn, sync_mode)?;
    } else {
        // Only per-connection, read-safe PRAGMAs.
        conn.execute_batch("PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON")?;
        conn.execute_batch("PRAGMA busy_timeout = 5000")?;
        conn.execute_batch("PRAGMA mmap_size = 0")?;
        conn.execute_batch("PRAGMA temp_store = MEMORY")?;
    }
    Ok(())
}

// Silence-unused warning when checkpoint is not yet used.
fn _keep_checkpoint_interval_linked(_path: &Path, _i: Option<Duration>) {
    let _ = PathBuf::new();
}
```

